.TH "tpm_chip_alloc" 9 "tpm_chip_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tpm_chip_alloc \- allocate a new struct tpm_chip instance
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct tpm_chip *" tpm_chip_alloc
.BI "(struct device *pdev "  ","
.BI "const struct tpm_class_ops *ops "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
device to which the chip is associated
At this point pdev mst be initialized, but does not have to
be registered
.IP "ops" 12
struct tpm_class_ops instance
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocates a new struct tpm_chip instance and assigns a free
device number for it. Must be paired with put_device(\fIchip->dev\fP).
